    <div class="third-card-text">
      <h2 class="third-card-header">President & Founder</h2>
      <div class="third-card-line"></div>
      <div class="third-card-paragraph">
        <p>
          Josette Zahinda is President and founding member of My Child and Me,
          a nonprofit organization dedicated to stabilizing families by elevating
          the quality of life of the abandoned mothers with their children presently in Congo DR. &nbsp;
          For the past 19 years, she has worked in the sales and customer service departments for United Airlines.
        </p>
        <p>
          Josette is a mother of three children. When Josette was pregnant with her third child,
          she found herself with two young children in a women shelter due to domestic violence.
          That experience led her to become a strong advocate for women and children victims of
          domestic violence. &nbsp;Josette presently serves on the Board of Directors for the
          Loudoun Citizen for Social Justice also known as LAWS, an organization that provides
          assistance to victims of domestic violence and sexual assault in Virginia.
          &nbsp;Josette holds a bachelors degree in Christian education and an MBA.
        </p>
      </div>
